Project Overview

This project performs a statistical analysis of business sales data to understand sales behavior, marketing impact, and revenue patterns.
The analysis uses descriptive statistics, hypothesis testing, correlation analysis, confidence intervals, and regression modeling to generate meaningful business insights.

This project demonstrates how statistics can support data-driven decision making in real-world business scenarios.

ğŸ¯ Project Objectives

Analyze sales data using descriptive statistics

Understand the relationship between marketing spend and sales

Perform hypothesis testing to validate business assumptions

Calculate confidence intervals for sales estimates

Build a regression model to predict sales

Translate statistical results into business insights

